\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
The Monster
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Tim Min
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Monster awaits its chance to strike.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

It patiently plots its fatal attack.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

It preys on weak and strong ones alike, 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

As nothing survives its vicious stab.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Monster observes his prey with great care.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

After all, it muses, it's all just a game: 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

A quest to destroy! Not one will it spare! 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

And yet, he laments, it's sad all the same.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"What a shame!" it thinks, having found the prey's kinks.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

"A good one, this is! But alas, begone!" 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Its powerful blow is thrown in a blink; 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The victim lies dead, the Monster just yawns.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Again, I will strike," the Monster confirms.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

"With each success comes such great returns!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Monster, yet again, awaits its chance to strike.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
His victims' names, he mocks them in song:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Dreams, the pathways that lead us astray!" 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

"Innocence, the wall that sheltered childhood days!" 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

"Passion, the flame that burns the fuel in our hearts!" 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

"Joy, the lie which hides that life is a farce!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the Monster suddenly falls to its knees.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

It cries and screams, to no avail.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

It fades out slowly, 'til there's nothing to see.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

It poofs from existence with a final wail.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Closer and closer we inch to this fall, 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

For this terrific beast is a part of us all.
 
\end_layout

\end_body
